Venezuelan President  Hugo Chavez 
accepted an offer from Brazilian President  Dilma Rousseff  to
receive treatment for cancer in  Sao Paulo ,  Folha de S. Paulo 
reported, without saying where it obtained the information.  Chavez may be treated at the Sirio Libanes hospital, the
newspaper said. Rousseff and Paraguayan President Fernando Lugo
received cancer treatment there in 2009 and 2010 respectively.  To contact the reporters on this story:
